# CRITICAL -- NEVER VIOLATE THESE RULES

## Locked Auth Routes -- DO NOT MODIFY WITHOUT EXPLICIT APPROVAL
- handleGoogleOAuthCallback -> /auth/callback/google
- handleGitHubOAuthCallback -> /api/oauth/github/callback
Breaking these locks ALL users out of the dashboard.
Before touching either function, paste the full current code and wait for approval.

## OAuth Flow Architecture
- Both flows use KV SESSION_CACHE for state storage
- connectDrive: true in KV state = Google Drive connection from agent popup
- connectGitHub: true in KV state = GitHub connection from agent popup  
- No flag present = login flow -> must redirect to /dashboard after session creation
- NEVER use getAuthUser() to distinguish login vs connection flows

## Other Locked Files
- Repo root `wrangler.production.toml` (main worker) -- never modify without Sam confirming
- Main worker deploy never uses a repo-root `wrangler.toml` for production; use `wrangler.production.toml` only as configured in this project.

## ABSOLUTE DEPLOY RULES — NEVER DEVIATE

MCP server deploys:
- Worker name: inneranimalmedia-mcp-server (EXACT — no variations)
- Path in this monorepo: `inneranimalmedia-mcp-server/`
- Command: `npx wrangler deploy -c wrangler.toml` (from `inneranimalmedia-mcp-server/` only). **Never** run bare `wrangler deploy` there: the monorepo root `wrangler.jsonc` (`inneranimalmedia`) would be used and would deploy the wrong worker.
- `inneranimalmedia-mcp-server/wrangler.toml` field `name` MUST be `inneranimalmedia-mcp-server` — verify before every deploy
- If `wrangler.toml` is missing or `name` is wrong: STOP and tell Sam

Main worker deploys:
- Worker name: inneranimalmedia
- Repo: march1st-inneranimalmedia/ (this repo)
- Command: `./scripts/with-cloudflare-env.sh npx wrangler deploy -c wrangler.production.toml`
- Never use plain `npx wrangler deploy` at this repo root (wrong worker / config)

## Deploy queue and post-deploy verification
- **Maximum 2 queue items per deploy** — do not batch more than two deploy-related tasks into a single approval/deploy cycle; split work across sessions or explicit approvals if needed.
- **After every deploy:** verify the current project’s primary surface loads in the browser (e.g. `/dashboard/agent` on production, or whatever URL matches this repo/build) **before** approving or starting the next item in the deploy queue. No chained deploys without a successful load check on the relevant page.

FORBIDDEN ACTIONS — these require Sam's explicit approval in chat:
- Creating any new Cloudflare Worker
- Creating any new D1 database
- Creating any new R2 bucket
- Running `wrangler secret put` or touching any secret
- Deploying any worker not named `inneranimalmedia` or `inneranimalmedia-mcp-server`

If Cursor is about to create a new Cloudflare resource that did not exist before, STOP completely and ask Sam: "I'm about to create [X]. Is this intentional?"

When Sam restricts scope to main worker + R2 only (no MCP deploy), only these are allowed:
```bash
./scripts/with-cloudflare-env.sh npx wrangler deploy -c wrangler.production.toml
./scripts/with-cloudflare-env.sh npx wrangler r2 object put agent-sam/static/dashboard/mcp.html --file=dashboard/mcp.html --content-type=text/html --remote -c wrangler.production.toml
./scripts/with-cloudflare-env.sh npx wrangler r2 object put agent-sam/static/dashboard/mcp-workflows-panel.js --file=static/dashboard/mcp-workflows-panel.js --content-type=application/javascript --remote -c wrangler.production.toml
```
Never overwrite `agent-sam/static/dashboard/agent/agent-dashboard.js` except from the Vite build output. There is no Worker named `inneranimalmedia-mcp` (that string may appear as a service id in D1 only).

## SCOPE ENFORCEMENT (non-negotiable)

- When given a file to change, ONLY change that file
- If you find related issues in OTHER files, list them as "Found in [file]: [issue]" but DO NOT touch them
- Never build, rebuild, or upload files not explicitly named
- Never run npm install, npm build, or R2 uploads unless explicitly told to
- Never touch overview-dashboard/, dist/, or R2 unless the prompt says "deploy frontend" or "upload to R2"
- One file per change unless prompt explicitly says "also fix in [other file]"
- If scope expands beyond what was asked, STOP and ask "I found X in Y file, should I fix that too?"

MANDATORY before any deploy:

- List every file changed
- List every file uploaded to R2
- If either list has files not mentioned in the prompt, stop and confirm before proceeding
